My personal understanding is that the entire story, from Chapter 1 onwards, was all an elaborate hallucination, resulting presumably from the powerful sedatives the man is subjected to by the crazy daughter with which she can have her way with him. That could explain why or how the selfie was taken in the first place. The uneasy look from the mom at the end tells me that she's aware of this, effectively a "hostage" like her husband (who seems to have had only an inkling of this from the shocking reveal on his phone) to the whims of their twisted daughter.

Those are my thoughts, anyway. The story itself is pretty vague and open-ended, which I think was the intention. Heck, people are still talking about that ending up to now.

This is all conjecture. I think the mother resents the dad cause he wouldn't stop pressuring her to get an abortion, so much in fact that she said "Yes" but ran away. I also don't think the mother made any "deal". A CEO/Board Member/Media Manager knew about the daughter and wanted some fun. The mother blackmailed the perpetrator for success so her family wouldn't be poor. Perp wanted seconds but mother knew if she told police he would reveal her blackmail so she hires the body guard. The daughter, after growing up hearing her mom talk shit about her dad, grows a sick attachment to him, the rape and subsequent success of the failing company made her paranoid and resentful. The dad, after the big reveal and getting stab then recovering, suffers from PTSD and chronic temporary memory loss with a case of mild dementia. His dream probably triggered this and when he woke up he thought everything was normal. Which also explains why to him everyone looks happy and smiling till they aren't.
